## Upcoming Major Space Launches

### SpaceX Falcon 9 - Starlink Group 12-10
- **Date/Time**: October 20, 2024, 07:49 UTC (NET, subject to change)
- **Location**: Cape Canaveral Space Force Station, SLC-40, Florida, USA
- **Payload**: 23 Starlink satellites (v2.1 Mini)
- **Details**: Routine Starlink deployment mission. First stage booster (B1085) on 24th flight, landing on drone ship.
- **Source**: [SpaceX Launches](https://www.spacex.com/launches/mission/?missionId=sl-12-10) | [NextSpaceflight](https://nextspaceflight.com/launches/)

### SpaceX Falcon 9 - Starlink Group 10-11
- **Date/Time**: October 21, 2024, 02:19 UTC (NET)
- **Location**: Vandenberg Space Force Base, SLC-4E, California, USA
- **Payload**: 21 Starlink satellites (v2 Mini)
- **Details**: Booster B1071 on 13th flight.
- **Source**: [NextSpaceflight](https://nextspaceflight.com/launches/) | [Spaceflight Now](https://spaceflightnow.com/launch-schedule/)

### NASA/SpaceX Crew-9 (Postponed)
- **Date/Time**: No earlier than October 25, 2024 (TBD)
- **Location**: Kennedy Space Center, LC-39A, Florida, USA
- **Payload**: Crew Dragon Resilience with NASA astronauts Matthew Dominick, Michael Barratt, Jeanette Epps, and Roscosmos cosmonaut Aleksandr Grebenkin
- **Details**: Delayed due to Crew-8 return issues. ISS Expedition 72 relief crew.
- **Source**: [NASA](https://www.nasa.gov/mission/crew-9/) | [SpaceX](https://www.spacex.com/launches/mission/?missionId=crew-9)

## Recent Launches
- **October 17, 2024**: SpaceX Falcon 9 launched 20 Starlink satellites from SLC-40 (successful).
- **October 15, 2024**: Rocket Lab Electron "Kinéis 4" from Māhia Peninsula, New Zealand (successful, final of 5 satellites).

For real-time updates: [RocketLaunch.Live](https://www.rocketlaunch.live/) | [NASA Launch Schedule](https://www.nasa.gov/launchschedule/) | [Spaceflight Now](https://spaceflightnow.com/launch-schedule/). Schedules can change due to weather/technical issues.
